## 1. Reconnaissance & Enumeration (Nmap, Wfuzz, Droopscan)

The initial phase focuses on discovering running services, hidden web content, and known vulnerabilities.

### 🔍 Service Discovery (Nmap)

The goal is to find all open ports and determine service versions.

| Action | Command | Output/Notes |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Full Port Scan** | `nmap -p 65535 -sV -sC [Target IP] --open` | **Ports Found:** 22 (SSH - OpenSSH), 80 (HTTP - Apache, **Drupal 7**) |
| **OS Fingerprinting** | (Manual banner grab or Nmap results) | **Confirmed:** Linux (Debian) |

### 🌐 Web Enumeration (Wfuzz & Droopscan)

The target is running **Drupal 7** on port 80, making web-focused enumeration a priority.

| Tool | Purpose | Command | Finding |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Wfuzz (Directories)** | Fuzz for hidden directories. | `wfuzz -c -z file,/usr/share/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/raft-large-directories.txt -u http://[Target IP]/FUZZ/ --hc 404` | Standard Drupal structure (e.g., `/admin`, `/user`, `/sites`). |
| **Wfuzz (Files)** | Fuzz for hidden files. | `wfuzz -c -z file,/usr/share/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/raft-large-files.txt -u http://[Target IP]/FUZZ --hc 404` | Files like `install.php`, `update.php`. |
| **Droopscan** | Specifically scans Drupal installations. | `droopscan scan drupal -u http://[Target IP]` | Confirms **Drupal 7.67** and lists themes (`bartik`) and modules. |
| **Manual Inspection**| View source code and click links. | `View Page Source` & `robots.txt` | Identifies a `/contact` form (input source) and the URL parameter `nid=` on pages like `/node/1`. |

